	<dd><a name="comment_2438" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Ben</strong> replies:</em> You, the 16-year-old, you'll be 18 by the time any of these laws would be passed anyway, so it wouldn't affect you.  Also the vast majority of 16-17 year olds are not mature enough to make an informed decision on what parties to vote for and would frankly be a liability.</p> <p>Claire, the point is that we're not apathetic, we just don't want to vote.  I can't speak for everyone, but personally I don't think it's worthwhile.  I have read about each of the policies of the major 3 parties, as well as the Greens, and I find it hard to believe that they will deliver on the majority of them.<br />There's no point choosing when your choice results in pretty much the same thing.</p>
